            <title>[LUCENE-3665] Make WeightedSpanTermExtractor extensible to handle custom query implemenations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3665</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently if I have a custom query which subclasses query directly I can&apos;t use the QueryScorer for highlighting since it does explicit instanceof checks. In some cases its is possible to rewrite the query before passing it to the highlighter to obtain a primitive query. However I had the usecase where this was not possible ie. the original index was not available on the machine which highlights the results. To still use the highlighter I had to copy a bunch of code due to visibility issues in those classes. I think we can make this extensible with minor effort to allow this usecase without massive code duplication.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
